comments.body:
@Gary, since I haven't been able to reproduce this issue in anything other than our production environment (in which I'm not too comfortable running a SNAPSHOT), I may have to wait for the official 5.5 release.  I can't reproduce it locally with 5.4.2, let alone a newer snapshot.  :-)

FWIW, it has been a couple of weeks (and a couple of billion messages!) since we've seen this error in production with 5.4.2.  It comes and goes at random.  One week we'll have a couple of our servers hit this issue, the next week it's all hunky dory.

Looking forward to 5.5.  Thanks!
